				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\kappa }_{{\rm{latt}}}=\frac{1}{N{V}_{0}}\sum _{\lambda }{\kappa }_{\lambda }=\frac{1}{N{V}_{0}}\sum _{\lambda }{C}_{\lambda }{{\bf{v}}}_{\lambda }\otimes {{\bf{v}}}_{\lambda }{\tau }_{\lambda }$$\end{document}where N is the number of unit cells in the crystal (equivalent to the number of wavevectors included in the Brillouin zone summation) and V0 is the volume of the crystallographic unit cell. κλ contains the product of the modal heat capacity (Cλ), group velocity (vλ), and phonon mean-free path (vλ × τλ, where τλ is the phonon lifetime). Graphical analyses of the modal contributions to lattice thermal conductivity and the atomic force sets used for the thermal conductivity calculations were performed using the Phono3py-Power-Tool code56.

